Lagos – The positive performance on the floor of the Nigerian Stock Exchange (NSE) was sustained yesterday as the All Share Index (ASI) rose 0.8 per cent to settle at 39,167.39 points while year-to-date return strengthened to 2.4 per cent. The bullish performance was as a result of buying interest in large cap stocks – Dangote Cement (+1.4%), Nestle Nigeria (+3.1%) and Seplat petroleum Development Company (+8.1%). Accordingly, investors gained N116.6 billion as market capitalisation increased to N14.2 trillion. Although volume traded declined by 43.4 per cent to 341.5 million units, value traded rose 33.6 per cent to N5.2 billion. The top traded stocks by volume were United Capital (82.7m), Dangote Sugar Refinery (56.9m), and Africa Prudential (49.6m) while Guaranty Trust Bank (N1.9bn), Dangote Sugar Refinery (N1.2bn) and Dangote Cement (N522.7m) were the most traded stocks by value. While reacting at the close of trading, analysts at Afrinvest said: “We expect market performance to remain upbeat as investors continue to take position in market bellwethers currently trading at attractive entry prices.” Sector performance was largely bullish as all indices save the banking index which lost 0.4 per cent  due to profit taking in Access Bank (-1.8%), Zenith Bank (-0.4%) and Guaranty Trust Bank (-0.2%), closed in the green. The Oil and Gas index outperformed other indices as it reversed the negative performance from the last session), up 4.9 per cent, on the back of price appreciation in Seplat Petroleum Development Company (+8.1%) and Mobil Oil (+5.0%). The Insurance index followed suit as gains in NEM Insurance (+4.8%), Equity Assurance (+4.8%) and WAPIC Insurance (+4.2%) pushed the index 0.9 per cent higher. Similarly, the Industrial and Consumer Goods indices rose 0.5 per cent and 0.4 per cent  as a result of buying interest in Dangote Cement (+1.4%) and Nestle Nigeria (+3.1%) respectively. Investor sentiment as measured by market breadth (advance/decline ratio) softened to 1.3x from 1.5x in the preceding session as 37 stocks advanced compared to 21 stocks that declined. The top performing stocks were Seplat Petroleum Development Company (+8.1%), Mobil Oil (+5.0%) and NEM Insurance (+4.8%) while Prestige Assurance (-4.7%), Eterna Oil (-4.5%) and First City Monument Bank (-4.2%) were the worst performing stocks. comments Do you get a good or bad response from your wife after making love? Discover a great natural solution that changed my story and put an end to weak/premature ejaculation, CLICK HERE. 